    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.13_0001"/>
                
                <note>1958</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear John,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am shocked and saddened by the great loss that you have suffered. To lose the chosen companion whom one has loved and with whom he has shared this strange experience that we call life for so many years is to lose what is more precious than life itself; and only those who have had a like experience can sense its bewildering and crushing meaning.</p>
                
                <p>I trust that in the memory of your happy days, in your children, in your many friends, in your own stout heart you may find the courage to go bravely on.</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.13_0002"/>
                
                <p>I am yours in deep sympathy and fraternal feeling.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Albert E. Trombly</signed>
                
                    <dateline>April 18th</dateline>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
